1 pound Baby Carrots
2.25 ounce Mike’s Hot Honey®
1 ounce Garlic Herb Butter
1 teaspoon Cooking Oil
Salt
Pepper

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring garlic herb butter to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Toss carrots on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until tender and lightly browned, 18-22 minutes.

Remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss carrots with softened garlic herb butter and Mike's Hot Honey to taste.